Subject: Re: [T2] Tranny bushings, linkages, adjustments?

The pin bore in the base of the shift lever has a small coil spring
whose only function is to make reassembly more difficult.
Remove the pin and clean out the residue of old caked grease
and you will find it, or at least the counterbore in which it resides.
Dave \X/


